  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, boil half a kettle and take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Chop the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Chop the <strong>tomatoes</strong> into wedges and trim the <strong>green beans</strong></p><p>Peel and cut the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into wedges</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1695718530636-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1695718530636-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1695718530636-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1695718530636-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1695718530636-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong>, <strong>tomato wedges</strong> and <strong>onion wedges</strong> to a baking tray lined with <strong>tin foil </strong>(to avoid mess!)</p><p>Add the <strong>dried</strong> <strong>oregano </strong>with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and put the tray in the oven for an initial 25 min</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? Use 2 trays!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1695718534997-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1695718534997-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1695718534997-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1695718534997-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1695718534997-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cover the<strong> free range</strong> <strong>chicken breast portions</strong> in<strong> cling film</strong> and bash them with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> until evenly flattened to approx. 1cm in thickness</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1695718540611-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1695718540611-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1695718540611-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1695718540611-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1695718540611-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> on a large plate</p><p>Add the juice of 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>lemon</strong> to a bowl with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Stir everything together until the lemon and oil have combined – this is your <strong>lemon oil</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1695718546606-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1695718546606-x400.jpg",
